ve problems but, most of the time, I prefer Linux to Windows. Only occasionally do I need a Windows machine.</p> </div> </article> </li> </ul> </li> <li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="comment-4604"> <article itemprop="comment" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/UserComments"> <header class="comment-header"> <p class="comment-author" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"> <img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/01f815260e81547a4fd5205a55f0afe2?s=96&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D96&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='96'/><span itemprop="name">Craig Peace</span> <span class="says">says</span> </p> <p class="comment-meta"> <time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-03-09T21:57:00+00:00" itemprop="commentTime"><a href="http://journalxtra.com/linux/ubuntu-fixing-the-blank-screen-on-installation-bug/comment-page-1/#comment-4604" class="comment-time-link" itemprop="url">March 9, 2013 at 9:57 PM</a></time> </p> </header> <div class="comment-content" itemprop="commentText"> <p>your a star, thx was about to throw the machine out of the window</p> </div> <div class="comment-reply"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/linux/ubuntu-fixing-the-blank-screen-on-installation-bug/?replytocom=4604#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-4604", "4604", "respond", "2532")'>Reply</a></div> </article> <ul class="children"> <li class="comment even depth-2" id="comment-4605"> <article itemprop="comment" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/UserComments"> <header class="comment-header"> <p class="comment-author" itemprop="creator" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"> <img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/16d0cfe9932200068b8a7752b8bea45d?s=96&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D96&amp;r=R' class='avatar avatar-96 photo' height='96' width='